ill help take your SEO efforts to the next level.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we&#8217;ll show you how to switch from Yoast to All in One SEO in 2 simple steps. And don&#8217;t worry, we promise you wonâ€™t lose any of your valuable SEO data. We know how hard youâ€™ve worked to get to where you are&#8230;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;and fortunately, itâ€™s about to get even better!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But first, you may be wondering if itâ€™s okay to change an SEO plugin and what will happen to all your data? Weâ€™ll put your worries to rest next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Is It Okay to Change an SEO Plugin?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Itâ€™s definitely okay to change an SEO plugin, and it wonâ€™t hurt your rankings in search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As long as you migrate your prior SEO settings to AIOSEO, nothing will be lost. You can rest assured that AIOSEO will import all your metadata, such as SEO titles, meta descriptions, keywords, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You wonâ€™t have to write them all over again and go through the hassle of updating all your web pages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, it only takes 2 simple steps to do this using AIOSEO. And if youâ€™re currently using Rank Math instead of Yoast, the same steps work for that plugin as well.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, letâ€™s take a look at how to switch from Yoast to All in One SEO next.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Migrating From Yoast SEO to All in One SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"447\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/all-in-one-seo-homepage.png\" alt=\"The best WordPress SEO plugin, All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26967\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/all-in-one-seo-homepage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/all-in-one-seo-homepage-300x184.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/all-in-one-seo-homepage-600x367.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></fig